<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,847,1396]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,329,1109,1135]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species could be confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[823,969,1109,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amphion">
<emphasis box="[823,969,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. amphion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see the discussion of 
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1417,1109,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amphion">
<emphasis box="[1271,1417,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. amphion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[151,439,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignacio">
<emphasis box="[151,439,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Sphaeropthalma ignacio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuster" box="[620,807,1146,1172]" pageId="23" pageNumber="34" refString="Schuster, R. M. (1958) A revision of the sphaeropthalmine Mutillidae of America north of Mexico. II. Entomologica Americana, 37, 1 - 130." type="journal article" year="1958">
Schuster (
<number box="[737,798,1146,1172]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1958.0">1958</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<taxonomicName box="[888,1035,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicincta">
<emphasis box="[888,1035,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. albicincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group with 
<taxonomicName box="[1273,1365,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arota">
<emphasis box="[1273,1365,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. arota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helicaon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. helicaon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and many synonyms), 
<emphasis box="[531,966,1184,1209]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[531,692,1184,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coaequalis">S. coaequalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[705,837,1184,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nokomis">S. nokomis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[850,966,1184,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinales">S. pinales</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1024,1160,1184,1209]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1156,1184,1209]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisetosa">S. bisetosa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Based on morphology, similarities in genitalia and 
<bibRefCitation box="[475,680,1221,1247]" pageId="23" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P., Wilson, J. S. &amp; von Dohlen, C. D. (2010) Recent radiation in the Nearctic nocturnal Sphaeropthalmini velvet ants (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae) driven by Neogene Orogeny. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 56, 134 - 145." type="journal article">
Pitts 
<emphasis box="[534,593,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[608,672,1221,1247]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<taxonomicName box="[735,882,1221,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albicincta">
<emphasis box="[735,882,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. albicincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group should be split into two separate groups. 
<taxonomicName box="[248,543,1259,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignacio">
<emphasis box="[248,543,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Sphaeropthalma ignacio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed in the newly designated 
<taxonomicName box="[1059,1187,1259,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamyrus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1187,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. lamyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group along with 
<taxonomicName box="[211,315,1296,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacala">
<emphasis box="[211,315,1296,1321]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. jacala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was previously placed in its own species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Pitts" box="[985,1250,1296,1322]" pageId="23" pageNumber="34" refString="Pitts, J. P. &amp; Parker, F. D. (2005) Description of the female, redescription of the male, and host associations of the Nearctic species Sphaeropthalma jacala Schuster (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Zootaxa, 1011, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="2005">
Pitts and Parker, 
<number box="[1189,1250,1296,1322]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[1273,1402,1296,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamyrus">S. lamyrus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinales">S. pinales</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[298,900,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[298,432,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisetosa">S. bisetosa</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[444,717,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arota">Sphaeropthalma arota</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[730,895,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coaequalis">S. coaequalis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1092,1333,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nokomis">
<emphasis box="[960,1092,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. nokomis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be placed into the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arota">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. arota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group.
</paragraph>
